    "These embeddings can inadvertently reinforce existing biases as they learn from the prevailing language usage, including gendered language and stereotypes and embed co-occurence patterns in the representations of the word themselves.",
    "A recent study by Caliskan et al. (2022) investigating the extent of gender bias in static word embeddings revealed that the most common words and concepts are strongly associated with men more so than with women.",
